node.accessibility_caption: Photo by scisnap on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: text.

Photo by scisnap on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: text that says '@scisnap.in WHAT'S NEW? A rare group of stem cells that produce neutrophils in human bone marrow has now been tracked down by scientists at La Jolla nstitute for Immunology (LJI).A progenitor cell type that exists even earlier in neutrophil development was revealed by the new study. They were able to identify more specific protein markers on the surface of this early progenitor cell in this work. v'.

Photo by scisnap on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: text that says '@scisnap.in WHAT'S THE HISTORY? Neutrophils are very hard to study. They don't survive well outside the human body, and growing their stem cells is even harder making the study difficult as they can only live inside human bone marrow. Until now, scientists had been using only a few markers to track neutrophils over time, which makes this discovery of protein markers more important. IgCritjove'.

Photo by scisnap on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: text that says '@scisnap.in WHAT'S NEXT? Further research is required to see if neutrophils can be a drug target for COVID-19 or can be tied to prognosis. The exact mechanism that stops neutrophils reaching maturity has to be identified. Identifying the early progenitors was critical for trying to control or target these cells as elevated levels of neutrophils were found in both lungs and blood of severe COVID-19 patients. Iagtjove'.

Photo by scisnap on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: text that says '@scisnap.in FUN FACTS Researchers also found that a flood of immature neutrophils, including the early progenitor cells in the bloodstream is often accompanied in cases of lung and skin cancers. They noticed that these immature neutrophils change as they interact with tumor cells. However, how these changes affect cancer progression still remains unsolved. Image IaeCdilove'.

Photo by scisnap on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: text that says '@scisnap.in REFERENCES Thank you BioTecNika for a wonderful article about "For The First Time Scientists Track Down Early Progenitors Of Neutrophill" DM to know more! IageCreit:jove'.

node.text:
"Neutrophils are the warriors of the immune system, always ready to fight off diseases and help heal injuries. But all immature neutrophils are not warriors; some of them could be dangerous turncoats. High levels of neutrophils in the blood can be a sign of cancer or even due to COVID-19 infection." ~ BioTecNika

Video by RT en Español on August 22, 2020. Paul Chodas, director del Centro de Estudios de Objetos Cercanos a la Tierra (CNEOS) de la NASA explicó que la gravedad de la Tierra cambió el rumbo del asteroide 2020 QG, que el pasado 15 de agosto pasó a tan solo 2.950 kilómetros del planeta, convirtiéndose en el encuentro más cercano conocido con una roca espacial que no llegó a impactar con la Tierra.

En el caso del 2020 QG, el asteroide resultó ser una sorpresa, ya que nadie lo había previsto. Con un tamaño de entre 3 y 6 metros de diámetro, pasó a una velocidad de 44.440 Km/h y no se consideró potencialmente peligroso. La NASA clasifica como peligroso cualquier objeto de un tamaño superior a los 150 metros y que se aproxime a la Tierra a menos de 7,5 millones de kilómetros.

Video by RT en Español on August 22, 2020. El empresario y fundador de Space X declaró el 18 de agosto que el motor Raptor del cohete Starship batió un récord mundial tras alcanzar los 330 bar en la cámara de presión con éxito. El récord anterior lo ostentaba el motor RD-701 fabricado por la Unión Soviética en los años 80.

La compañía planea usar seis de estos motores para despegar su nave espacial Starship con la intención de llevar al espacio hasta 150 toneladas de carga y personas en cada uno de sus trayectos a Marte, alrededor de la Luna y otros lugares del cosmos. Space X desea realizar un vuelo no tripulado al planeta rojo en 2022 y otro tripulado do saños más tarde.

node.text:
Ketika salah satu anggota keluarga terpapar virus korona, maka perlu diterapkan isolasi mandiri. Beberapa hal perlu diperhatikan bagi anggota keluarga lain dalam membantu proses penyembuhan pasien COVID-19 ini. Pasalnya, virus ini sangat mudah menyebar melalui droplets juga udara sehingga perlu waspada.

Dalam merawat pasien COVID-19, anggota keluarga lain perlu membantu pasien untuk mengikuti saran dari dokter, termasuk mematuhi protokol kesehatan untuk tetap berada di dalam rumah. Selain itu, juga mengingatkan agar pasien banyak istirahat serta mencukupi kebutuhan air mineral dalam tubuh.

Makanan bergizi juga perlu disiapkan dengan baik, pasalnya, pasien COVID-19 kerap kehilangan nafsu makan. Asupan nutrisi yang baik akan membuat sistem kekebalan tubuh meningkat.

Hal lain yang tak kalah penting adalah senantiasa mengonsumsi obat yang sudah diresepkan oleh dokter agar tubuh kembali sehat. Selain itu, sebaiknya perbaiki pula ventilasi rumah dengan baik, lebih baik jika membuka jendela agar sirkulasi udara berjalan dengan baik.

Selama proses perawatan, orang sekitar perlu memerhatikan kondisi pasien seperti gejala yang tak menghilang, terus demam dan mulai kesulitan bernafas. Bahkan kondisi psikis pasien juga perlu diperhatikan, anggota keluarga lainnya lebih baik memberikan dukungan mental dan emosi karena proses penyembuhan bisa membuat pasien stres dan merasa kesepian.

Pihak Perawat Sebaiknya Tetap Waspada

Saat merawat pasien isolasi mandiri, pihak keluarga atau rekan yang merawat juga tetap perlu waspada dengan memperhatikan diri sendiri untuk tetap sehat. Protokol kesehatan harus senantiasa dipatuhi, seperti dalam mengenakan masker yang harus tetap dikenakan ketika merawat, termasuk sebisa mungkin terus jaga jarak satu meter.

Simak ulasan lengkapnya di www.rs-alirsyadsurabaya.co.id

node.text:
How long could the coronavirus pandemic last? It's hard to say, but the head of the World Health Organization hopes the outbreak will be over within two years. ⁠
⁠
"Especially," he said in a media briefing, "if we can pool our efforts together and with national unity, global solidarity -- that's really key -- with utilizing the available tools to the maximum and hoping that we can have additional tools like a vaccine, I think that we can finish it in a shorter time than the 1918 flu."⁠
⁠
The 1918 flu pandemic lasted about two years and two months, and came in multiple waves. According to the CDC, as many as 500 million people worldwide were infected, and 50 million died of the disease.⁠

node.text:
? Wie ihr bereits mitbekommen habt, haben wir vor, ein Halal Gym zu errichten.

Bei Erreichen von 20.000 Abonnenten beginnen wir aktiv mit der Planung.

Um dieses Vorhaben zu unterstützen und gleichzeitig hilfsbedürfiten Menschen zu helfen, haben sich die Geschwister von @whipso_foundation bei uns gemeldet und den Vorschlag unterbreitet, dieses Vorhaben mit einer Spendenaktion zu kombinieren.

So kannst du mit nur wenig Mühe das Vorhaben des Halal Fitnessstudios und zugleich  des Brunnenbaus in Tansania unterstützen.

Für jeden Teilnehmer werden 50 Cent für einen Brunnen in Tansania gespendet.

Folgende Bedingungen müssen erfüllt werden:
1. Folge den Seiten @halal.fit und @whipso_foundation 
2. Teile den Beitrag in der Story und markiere  @halal.fit und @whipso_foundation 
3. Markiere 3 Freunde in dem Kommentarfeld.

Die Aktion geht bis einschließlich den 12.09.2020 um 23.59. 

Also lasst uns unser Ziel erreichen und im selben Zug hilfsbedürftige Menschen unterstützen!

node.text:
O Conselho Regional de Psicologia de São Paulo convida as psicólogas/os e a sociedade para dialogarmos sobre a "Psicologia nos tempos atuais" afirmando que a Psicologia é para todo mundo e se faz com Direitos Humanos!
 
Neste encontro especial, em comemoração ao Dia da/o Psicóloga/o e aos 58 anos da Psicologia no Brasil, manifestamos o nosso reconhecimento e agradecimento à atuação das/os psicólogas/os sobretudo nos tempos de pandemia. 

No atual contexto de nossas vidas, nos preocupamos com os afetos e cuidados como possibilidade de manifestação da resistência na afirmação do vínculo indissociável entre Psicologia e Direitos Humanos. 

Com o objetivo de valorizar, com afeto, o cuidado e resistência da Psicologia neste momento histórico de crise e sofrimentos, trazemos este diálogo como reconhecimento da contribuição cientifica e profissional, nas diferentes formas de ser e existir da Psicologia, potencializada nesta variedade de áreas, atuações e cuidados com as pessoas. 

Para tal, temos como nossas convidadas Lourdes Alves de Souza; Sandra Maria Taiar; Carmem Miriam Nunes da Rocha, e a mediação de Ivani Francisco de Oliveira.

Veja mais informações sobre este evento e as/os participantes pelo link nos Stories.

Mad appreciation to this dude right here, after he saw me snapping shots of him I had my mom translate that I was a photographer. Just before we had left he stood posted and smiled and said here take this picture. He saw some random dude with a camera and volunteered to help after seeing what I was doing. The amount of love and support from this trip was insane. Not only with family but with strangers as well. I’m proud to be Puerto Rican and I’m so happy I can say this is where my family comes from. Btw I had printed out these photos the third you’ll see in the next post, I wasn’t able to give them to him directly but I had someone ( @blessbembaflow ) do me a favor and give them to him the next time he saw him. Photo by Project Kaagaz on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'According to UNICEF, every 5th migrant in India is child. The Census of 2011 shows that there are 92.95 million child migrants dispersed across the country, with present figures likely to be much higher. Thisis double the number that was originally recorded in the Census of 1991 Child migrants are not a homogeneous category and vary in their reasons for movement. While migration for some has led to the creation of social and economic opportunities for most it is associated with serious risks PROJECT KAAGAZ'.

Photo by Project Kaagaz on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'The children who migrate with their parents live under constant uncertainty about their education, healthcare, nutrition and sanitation. There is no consistency in their standards ofliving. While some attend Anganwadis and tuitions nearby for the time period ftheir parents' stoppage, some are engaged in labour support their household incomes. 20 million child migrants under the age of 14 are said to be engaged in labour PROJECT KAAGAZ'.

Photo by Project Kaagaz on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'Children who stay back in rural areas while the parents move to cities for work are largely dependent on the parents for the food and security. Some are forced to engage in farming or other daily wage labour under harsh conditions and low pay, whereas others may depend upon the government or are at the mercy of their exploitative landlords or neighbours According to the Census of of2011, 56% of the migrant children are located in rural locations. This figure has only risen since the spread of the Coronavirus crisis PROJECT KAAGAZ'.

Photo by Project Kaagaz on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'Post the imposition of a lockdown on means fdaily earnings for most migrant labour, images of millions of families travelling hundreds of kilometres on foot surfaced the internet over 3 months ago. Instances of fatalities and visuals of children in tow shook the entire nation Millions of people who had left for urban spaces with the hopes of better livelihood have now returned home in the hopes of sustainence. PROJECT KAAGAZ'.

Photo by Project Kaagaz on August 22, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'With schools shut and their parents having suffered job losses, an creasing number of children are seen working under physically and mentally strenuous situations for relatively lower wages Education for these children has suffered majorly due to the inaccessibility to phones and internet. Earning enough for a meal a day has become a lot more important than coping with their school curriculum. The inadequacy ofresources and nutrition continues to be a problem for them PROJECT KAAGAZ'.
